A porn star who claims she had sex with Donald Trump sued the US president on Tuesday to invalidate a nondisclosure agreement over their alleged affair. Trump's lawyer has denied the president ever had an affair with Stormy Daniels, whose real name is Stephanie Clifford. Trump has been married to Melania Trump since 2005. Read more: Stormy Daniels: Trump lawyer 'paid $130,000' to porn actress The details of the case: The alleged affair took place after Trump married Melania Trump in 2005 Stormy's story: Clifford first spoke about having an affair with Trump in an interview with the US magazine In Touch. The actress said a sexual relationship shortly after Trump's wife Melania gave birth to their son. The magazine said the former porn star subsequently passed a lie detector test. amp/rt (AP, AFP)